section.section:
The contract for operating a child care center shall require the child care provider:
to be responsible for entering into agreements, and making arrangements with the employees, for the provision of child care;
to provide proof of financial responsibility;
to be licensed under Part VII and this Part VIII of this subtitle;
to comply with any laws or regulations governing child care centers;
to obtain and keep in effect liability insurance in an amount determined to be sufficient by the State Superintendent; and
to comply with any other requirement the State Superintendent considers reasonable and necessary.
